# Hint Ladder

This is one of the biggest missing pieces.

Research on tutoring systems shows:

# Weak-to-Strong Hints

outperform:

immediate answers.

Students retain more.

---

Your system should NEVER jump:

```text
wrong
→ answer
```

Instead:

---

# Hint Ladder Architecture

Three levels.

---

## Hint 1

Light Prompt

Purpose:

attention redirection.

Example:

```text
Look carefully at the denominator.
```

---

## Hint 2

Strategy Hint

Purpose:

suggest process.

Example:

```text
Count how many equal parts exist first.
```

---

## Hint 3

Near-Solution Hint

Purpose:

guided solve.

Example:

```text
There are 4 equal parts and 1 is shaded.
```

Only then:

solution reveal.

